# Copy to `.env.local` and fill in. Never commit real keys.
#
# CoinGecko key types — use the RIGHT one for each variable:
#
#  Pro key  (starts with CG- on a paid plan, root: pro-api.coingecko.com)
#    → Set as VITE_COINGECKO_PRO_API_KEY
#    → Unlocks /api/v3/onchain endpoints: pool lookup, OHLCV, etc.
#    → Chart requests route via /coingecko-pro-api proxy in dev
#
#  Demo key (starts with CG- on the free Demo plan, root: api.coingecko.com)
#    → Set as VITE_COINGECKO_DEMO_API_KEY
#    → ~30 req/min on general CoinGecko endpoints (prices, metadata)
#    → Does NOT unlock /onchain OHLCV or pool endpoints (Pro-only)
#    → Chart data still uses public GeckoTerminal (~10 req/min) when no Pro key
#
# Leaving both blank is fine — charts fall back to the public GeckoTerminal
# API (10 req/min) with automatic rate limiting and 65 s back-off on 429.
#
# Optional: minimum gap (ms) between throttled public Gecko requests (default 6000).
# Lower = faster chart polling / pool fallbacks, higher 429 risk vs ~10 req/min cap.

VITE_GECKO_MIN_GAP_MS=
VITE_COINGECKO_PRO_API_KEY=
VITE_COINGECKO_DEMO_API_KEY=
